# SQL Aggregation function - MIN/MAX

# Understanding MIN and MAX functions

> MIN function: Returns the minimum value from a set of values.
> MAX function: Returns the maximum value from a set of values.

# Syntax
SELECT MIN(column_name)
FROM table_name;

SELECT MAX(column_name)
FROM books;

# Example:
1. Using the MAX function:
To find the most recent release year in the books table:
SELECT MAX(released_year)
FROM books;

2. Using the MIN function:
To found the earliest release year in the books table:
SELECT MAX(released_year)
FROM books;

These functions are essential for quickly identifying the range of values within our dataset,
such as teh oldest and newest entries.

